						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1354, Parīdhāvi, Kārtika, śu. 1, Śu[kravāra],</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1432 October 24, Saturday,</hi> f.d.t. ·38, in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Dēvarāya-Mahārāya.</hi> It records that the king abolished the cess on marriages among all castes in <hi rend="bold">Koṭapi.</hi> It also states that those who marry and go out, keeping the Basava (on the pillar on which the inscription is engraved) to their right, will be blessed with many children.</p>						

						<p>First Face.</p>						

						</summary>
